>ORGANICS</b>=20
                <br>
                In the past few issues of Organic Bytes, the OCA has been a=
lerting=20
                its readers to contact various congressional subcommittees =
who=20
                are in the process of allocating funding for the 2007 Farm =
Bill.=20
                This massive piece of legislation provides funding until 20=
12=20
                and includes a variety of programs that would benefit organ=
ic=20
                farmers, sustainable agriculture and the environment. Thank=
s to=20
                your efforts and the concerted work of OCA's allies, many o=
f these=20
                target programs have been allocated funding.</font> </p>
              </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td width=3D"13%" height=3D"72">=20
              <div align=3D"center"><img src=3D"http://www.organicconsumers=
.org/images/bytes/farmer6.jpg" width=3D"90" height=3D"203"></div>
            </td>
            <td width=3D"87%" height=3D"72">=20
              <p><font size=3D"2" face=3D"Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-s=
erif">Specifically,=20
                the following funding has been approved in subcommittees fo=
r organic=20
                and sustainable agriculture related programs over the cours=
e of=20
                the next five years:</font></p>
              <ul>
                <li><font size=3D"2" face=3D"Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, san=
s-serif">$150=20
                  million to examine optimal conservation and environmental=
 outcomes=20
                  for organically produced agricultural products, and to de=
velop=20
                  new and improved seed varieties that are particularly sui=
ted=20
                  for organic agriculture.<br>
                  </font></li>
                <li><font size=3D"2" face=3D"Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, san=
s-serif">$22=20
                  million to help farmers pay for organic certification</fo=
nt></li>
                <li><font size=3D"2" face=3D"Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, san=
s-serif">$5=20
                  million for outreach to organic and specialty crop produc=
ers.</font></li>
                <li><font size=3D"2" face=3D"Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, san=
s-serif">$3=20
                  million to collect market and production data about organ=
ic=20
                  farming.</font></li>
              </ul>
              <p><font size=3D"2" face=3D"Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-s=
erif">The=20
                OCA will continue to alert you to new issues arising in thi=
s arena,=20
                as the 2007 Farm Bill continues to be developed by Congress=
. <br>
                <font size=3D"1"><b>Learn more:</b> <a href=3D"http://alert=
s.organicconsumers.org/trk/click?ref=3Dzqtbkk3um_1-b4x311cx3=
340774&" targe=
t=3D"_blank">http://www.organicconsumers.org/farm.cfm</a></font></font></p>
