            <td width=3D"83%" height=3D"153">=20
              <p><font size=3D"2" face=3D"Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-s=
erif"><b>RECENT=20
                HISTORY OF USDA ORGANIC LAWBREAKING</b><br>
                <i>January 2005 (Strike One):</i> Federal court rules that =
the=20
                USDA has violated federal regulations in allowing conventio=
nal=20
                and synthetic ingredients in products labeled as =
&quot;orga=
nic&quot;.</font></p>
              <p><font size=3D"2" face=3D"Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-s=
erif"><i>May=20
                2007 (Strike Two):</i> After heavy lobbying from industry, =
USDA=20
                proposed to allow 38 conventionally grown ingredients in fo=
ods=20
                labeled as organic. One of those ingredients, fish oil, has=
 never=20
                undergone review, which is a violation of federal law.</fon=
t></p>
              <p><font size=3D"2" face=3D"Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-s=
erif"><i>June=20
                2007 (Strike Three):</i> A federal judge had given the USDA=
 until=20
                midnight Friday (6/8) to post its final ruling, which the a=
gency=20
                failed to do.</font></p>
            </td>
